root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>805</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>axt-002Q</fr:addr><fr:route>axt-002Q.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Spectral locale in UF</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>11</fr:month><fr:day>1</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="ayberkt.xml"
type="local"
addr="ayberkt">Ayberk Tosun</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="martin-escardo.xml"
type="local"
addr="martin-escardo">Martín H. Escardó</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
  A <fr:link
href="axt-0008.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0008"><fr:tex>( \mathcal {U} ,  \mathcal {V} ,  \mathcal {W} )</fr:tex>-locale</fr:link> <fr:tex>X</fr:tex> is called <fr:strong>spectral</fr:strong>
  if it satisfies the following three conditions.
  <fr:ol><fr:li>It is a compact locale (i.e. the empty meet is compact).</fr:li>
    <fr:li>The meet of two compact opens is compact.</fr:li>
    <fr:li>
      For every <fr:tex>U :  \mathcal {O}( X )</fr:tex>, there exists a directed <fr:tex>\mathcal {W}</fr:tex>-family
      <fr:tex>(K_U,  \kappa _U)</fr:tex> that satisfies the following conditions.
      <fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex>(K_U,  \kappa _U)</fr:tex> is directed.</fr:li>
        <fr:li><fr:tex>U =  \bigvee _{k : K_U}  \kappa _U(k)</fr:tex>.</fr:li>
        <fr:li>
          It consists of compact opens i.e.
          <fr:tex>\forall  k : K_U. \  \mathsf {isCompact}( \kappa _{U}(k) )</fr:tex>.
        </fr:li></fr:ol></fr:li></fr:ol></fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:p>
  Notice the relationship of the third condition here to
  <fr:link
href="axt-0029.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0029">pseudocontinuity</fr:link>. If we formulate a notion of “pseudoalgebraicity”
  i.e. the analogue of <fr:link
href="axt-0029.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0029">pseudocontinuity</fr:link> for
  <fr:link
href="axt-001L.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001L">algebraicity</fr:link>, we could use that to avoid the repetition here
  because they are exactly the same thing. This is not good for presentation
  purposes (as for as locale theory is concerned), however, so it should
  probably be recorded as an equivalence.
</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
