show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>870</fr:anchor><fr:addr>axt-002L</fr:addr><fr:route>axt-002L.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Preliminary notions</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>10</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="ayberkt.xml"
type="local"
addr="ayberkt">Ayberk Tosun</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="martin-escardo.xml"
type="local"
addr="martin-escardo">Martín H. Escardó</fr:link></fr:contributor><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="tom-de-jong.xml"
type="local"
addr="tom-de-jong">Tom de Jong</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
  In our presentation here, we decouple the notion of a basis for a
  <fr:link
href="axt-0021.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0021"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:link> from any kind of compactness or relative compactness
  requirements.
</fr:p><fr:p>
  In the context of domain theory, the natural notion of basis <fr:em>should</fr:em>
  include such requirements (see for example <fr:link
href="axt-001U.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001U"><fr:strong>Defn. 2.2.3</fr:strong> of Abramsky and
  Jung</fr:link>). As our presentation here is intended to be applicable to a
  class of lattices broader than that of dcpos, however, we attempt to keep the
  presentation free of bias towards a specific
  <fr:link
href="https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/concept+with+an+attitude"
type="external">attitude</fr:link>. This is
  our motivation for the aforementioned decoupling.
</fr:p><fr:p>
  When the notion of a <fr:link
href="axt-0021.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0021"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:link> attains a specific
  <fr:link
href="https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/concept+with+an+attitude"
type="external">attitude</fr:link>, such as
  <fr:link
href="axt-0003.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0003">that of a denotational domain</fr:link>, it is perfectly fine for these
  terms to be overloaded to refer to concepts that include these requirements.
</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>862</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>axt-0022</fr:addr><fr:route>axt-0022.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Intensional basis for a <fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>10</fr:month><fr:day>26</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="tom-de-jong.xml"
type="local"
addr="tom-de-jong">Tom de Jong</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="martin-escardo.xml"
type="local"
addr="martin-escardo">Martín H. Escardó</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="ayberkt.xml"
type="local"
addr="ayberkt">Ayberk Tosun</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
  Let <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> be a <fr:link
href="axt-0021.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0021"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:link>. An <fr:em>intensional basis for <fr:tex>D</fr:tex></fr:em> is a
  <fr:link
href="axt-001F.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001F"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-family</fr:link> <fr:tex>(B,  \beta )</fr:tex> on <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> satisfying the condition: for every
  element <fr:tex>x : D</fr:tex>, there is a specified directed <fr:link
href="axt-001F.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001F"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-family</fr:link>
  <fr:tex>(I_x,  \iota _x)</fr:tex> on the basis index <fr:tex>B</fr:tex> such that
  <fr:tex>x =  \bigvee  (I_x,  \beta   \circ   \iota _x).</fr:tex></fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>866</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>axt-0028</fr:addr><fr:route>axt-0028.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Extensional basis for a <fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>10</fr:month><fr:day>28</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="tom-de-jong.xml"
type="local"
addr="tom-de-jong">Tom de Jong</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="martin-escardo.xml"
