  Let <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> be a <fr:link
href="axt-0021.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0021"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:link>. An <fr:em>intensional basis</fr:em> <fr:tex>(B,  \beta )</fr:tex>
  for <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> is called an <fr:link
href="axt-0022.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0022">extensional basis</fr:link> if <fr:tex>\beta</fr:tex> is an
  <fr:link
href="axt-0036.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0036">embedding</fr:link>.
</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>874</fr:anchor><fr:addr>axt-002M</fr:addr><fr:route>axt-002M.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Terminology for domain theory</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>10</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="tom-de-jong.xml"
type="local"
addr="tom-de-jong">Tom de Jong</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="martin-escardo.xml"
type="local"
addr="martin-escardo">Martín H. Escardó</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="ayberkt.xml"
type="local"
addr="ayberkt">Ayberk Tosun</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
  In <fr:link
href="tom-de-jong.xml"
type="local"
addr="tom-de-jong">Tom de Jong</fr:link>'s <fr:link
href="tdj-thesis.xml"
type="local"
addr="tdj-thesis">thesis</fr:link> and his Agda formalization of domain
  theory, the term “structurally continuous” is used to mean a
  <fr:link
href="axt-0021.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0021"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:link> <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> equipped with a function giving, for every <fr:tex>x :   D</fr:tex>, a small directed family of elements way below <fr:tex>x</fr:tex>, giving <fr:tex>x</fr:tex> as its
  join.
</fr:p><fr:p>
  In the new terminology, this notion of “structure” involved in the continuity
  of a dcpo is made explicit by the following notion.
</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>732</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>axt-002H</fr:addr><fr:route>axt-002H.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Continuity datum for a <fr:link
href="axt-0021.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0021"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>10</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="tom-de-jong.xml"
type="local"
addr="tom-de-jong">Tom de Jong</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="martin-escardo.xml"
type="local"
addr="martin-escardo">Martín H. Escardó</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
  A <fr:em>continuity datum</fr:em> for a <fr:link
href="axt-0021.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0021"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:link> <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> is a function
  giving, for every <fr:tex>x : D</fr:tex>, a specified <fr:link
href="axt-001F.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001F"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-family</fr:link> <fr:tex>(K_x,    \kappa _x)</fr:tex> on <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> satisfying the following conditions.
  <fr:ol><fr:li>The family <fr:tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</fr:tex> is directed.</fr:li>
    <fr:li><fr:tex>x =  \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }_{k : K_x}  \kappa _x(k)</fr:tex>.</fr:li>
    <fr:li>For each <fr:tex>k : K_x</fr:tex>, <fr:tex>\kappa _x(k)  \ll  x</fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:p>
  Factoring this structure out into a definition of its own obviates the need to
  have a name for the notion of a “<fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo having a specified continuity
  datum”, which is what “structurally continuous” means. Even though the
  equivalence between <fr:link
href="axt-0027.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0027">structurally continuous</fr:link> and “having a
  specified <fr:link
href="axt-002H.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-002H">continuity datum</fr:link>” is completely trivial, we still record
  this in the following proposition to be able to explicitly refer to this
  terminological identity.
</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>735</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>axt-001K</fr:addr><fr:route>axt-001K.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>10</fr:month><fr:day>24</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="tom-de-jong.xml"
type="local"
addr="tom-de-jong">Tom de Jong</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source"><fr:strong>Defn 4.4.1</fr:strong> of <fr:link
href="tom-de-jong.xml"
type="local"
addr="tom-de-jong">de Jong</fr:link>'s <fr:link
href="tdj-thesis.xml"
type="local"
addr="tdj-thesis">PhD thesis</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
  A <fr:link
href="axt-0021.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0021"><fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:link> <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> having a specified <fr:link
href="axt-002H.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-002H">continuity datum</fr:link>
  is the same thing as <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> being <fr:link
href="axt-0027.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-0027">structurally continuous</fr:link>.
</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:p>
  By replacing the specified existence here with mere existence, we obtain the
  notion of a <fr:link
href="axt-002I.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-002I">continuous <fr:tex>\mathcal {V}</fr:tex>-dcpo</fr:link>. The terminology for this is
  unchanged (i.e. is the same as the terminology of <fr:link
href="tom-de-jong.xml"
type="local"
addr="tom-de-jong">Tom de Jong</fr:link>'s
  <fr:link
href="tdj-thesis.xml"
type="local"
addr="tdj-thesis">thesis</fr:link>).
</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>737</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>axt-002I</fr:addr><fr:route>axt-002I.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Continuous <fr:link
